Source:  Growing Fruit & Nuts in NZ
Author:  BAXTER & JONES
Vol / Page:  114
Edition:
Quote:  Japanese plums (<i>Prunus salicinus</i>). These large vigoorous trees came from China... Japanese plums have a shorter chilling requirement and therefore flower earlier than European plums. Japanese plums are better suited to New Zealand than European types.
